Argumentum ad Ignorantiam [appeal to ignorance] <br>
To recognize the fallacy of appeal to ignorance, look for a conclusion based upon an absence of proof or evidence.  Be aware of the two types of cases in which lack of evidence for S is relevant to the truth or falsity of S.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>But also, be aware that the onus of proof is on the claimant and that no one can prove a negative.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
However, if you wish to read over credible and valid information on nuclear devices, have a look at this link. In it you’ll find facts that are contradictory to the nuclear devices and their effects proposed by Orion.<br>
