In space heat is transferred only by direct radiation.<br>
Steel melts at 1800 c<br>
Let us calaculate how much steel is required to absorb <br>
all the energy released by the fission of 1 Kg of U 235 or Pu 239.<br>
By E= M C sqaured fissioning 1 kilogram of fuel will<br>
release :<br>
1 * 300,000,000 *300,000,000 /1000 joules of energy.<br>
This is  9 * 10 to the 16 th power devided by 1000.<br>
<br>
This is 9 * 10 to the 13th power. It takes 1,000,000 joules to heat 1 kg of steel to 1000 c . This leaves 9 * 10 the<br>
7 power joules.  This 90 000,000  joules.   It takes 1,000,000 ,000 joules to heat 1000 kg to 1000 C.<br>
<br>
 This 110 times more energy then is released by a 20 kiloton atomic explosion. 110 Times 20 kt = 2.2  megatons. <br>
This is how much energy 1000 kg of steel can absorb without heating above 1000 C. This means also that 10,000 kg of solid steel can withstand all the energy released by a 22 megaton thermonuclear explosion.<br>
Tim<br>
