1. Direct radiation <br>
2. Conduction <br>
3. Covection.<br>
Conduction and Cpnvection do not count in the case<br>
of nuclear explosions behind pusher plates on orions<br>
because the plasma is in contact with the plate for only a miniscule fraction of a second.For example:<br>
If I explode a 10 kiloton A-Bomb the debris velocity is 1,000,000 meter/second  . If It goes off 10 meters from the plate the time of contact with the plate is just 1/100,000th of a second. After that time the plasma has passed the plate and no longer has contact with it. At 1000 meters it takes 1/1000th of a second for contact with the plate.<br>
Direct radiation declines by the inverse sqaure law.<br>
Em such as heat radiation travels at light speed.<br>
 It will interact with the plate at 10 meters distance<br>
 for just 1/30,000,000,000th of a second. at 1000 meters<br>
the interaction is1/300,000th of a second.<br>
The strength of a shock wave from its source declines by the cube root  of the change in distance. For example Shock A <br>
is at 10,000 pis (pounds per sqauare inch at 1 meter from an<br>
explosion. At 10 meters from the explosion the strength of the shock wave has declined by 1000 times, because 10 cubed is 1000. <br>
These things are the physics that allows the impulse absorber plate of an orion nuclear pulse rocket to survive many atomic or thermonuclear explosions without being destroyed by the heat, and the blast effects.<br>
Tim<br>
